## Build and Test Commands

```powershell
# Install dependencies (first run only)
.\Build\build.ps1 -ResolveDependency

# Run all default tasks
.\Build\build.ps1

# Run Pester tests
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList Test

# Lint with PSScriptAnalyzer
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList Analyze

# Generate markdown + MAML help
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList Help

# Build a .nupkg artifact
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList BuildNuget
```

## Repository Layout

```
Public/          Exported functions — one .ps1 file per function
Private/         Internal helper functions — not exported
Tests/
  Unit/          Pester 5 unit tests (*Tests.ps1)
  Common/        Shared tests: manifest, help coverage, PSSA
Build/           build.ps1 entry, build.psake.ps1 tasks, build.depend.psd1
Documentation/   PlatyPS-generated markdown help
en-US/           Compiled MAML help (Get-Help output)
```

## Key Conventions

- One exported function per file; filename must match function name exactly
- All exported functions require comment-based help (`.SYNOPSIS`, `.DESCRIPTION`, `.PARAMETER`, `.EXAMPLE`)
- Use `[CmdletBinding()]` and `[OutputType()]` on all functions
- Construct all paths with `Join-Path` or `$PSScriptRoot`; never hardcode or concatenate paths
- Follow approved PowerShell verbs: https://learn.microsoft.com/powershell/scripting/developer/cmdlet/approved-verbs-for-windows-powershell-commands
- Target PowerShell 5.1+ compatibility unless documented otherwise

## Testing

Tests use **Pester 5** syntax: `Should -Be`, `Should -Not -BeNullOrEmpty`, `Should -Invoke`.

```powershell
# Run a single test file
Invoke-Pester -Path .\Tests\Unit\<FunctionName>.Tests.ps1 -Output Detailed
```

New test files go in `Tests\Unit\` and must match the `*Tests.ps1` pattern.

